The Addis Ababa city administration, in collaboration with the ministry of health, has intensified its medical surveillance at the airport. The World Health Organisation has declared the virus a global health emergency. 

Over 200 people have so far succumbed to the virus. China remains the most affected with over 9 500 reported cases. 

SABC's Coletta Wanjohi visited the airport in Addis Ababa...

